I’m an MS student at Georgia Tech in Computer Science with a specialization in Machine Learning. I received Bachelor's degrees in Computer Science and Physics, also from Georgia Tech, in 2016.

I’ve been working on clinical NLP with professors Jacob Eisenstein and Jimeng Sun, focusing on learning effective and interpretable document representations.

This summer, I'm an intern in the Natural Language group at ISI, working with Jonathan May and Nanyun Peng on a project in commonsense reasoning and language grounding.

In the summer of 2017 I worked as a data science intern at Zappos.com on machine learning problems, including classifying user behavior using clickstream data.

I also have a nascent blog. I'm trying to improve my writing, so I'd love to know your thoughts!
